Animated instanced lights via a cached Point Instancer

Three SphereLights are instanced through a PointInstancer with time-sampled
positions, sweeping the lit pools across the ground plane from frame 1 to
frame 30. Through the Hydra render delegate (Solaris), scrubbing the timeline
must move the instanced lights with the instancer. Before the fix the lights
stayed frozen at their frame-1 positions because the Arnold instancer was only
rebuilt on HdLight::DirtyParams and not when the instancer itself was dirty.

This is an interactive (re-render / time-scrub) bug: a single batch render
rebuilds the instancer on the first Sync, so it cannot reproduce the freeze.
Verify in Houdini/Solaris by scrubbing the timeline. The batch render here only
guards the instanced-light code path from breaking.

Fixes #2641

author: cyril.pichard@autodesk.com

PARAMS: {'scene':'test.usda', 'kick_params': '-frame 16'}
